<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Abject1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ábject,</orth> adj., mean, despicable: <bibl n="shak. err 4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 34.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 128</bibl> <cit><quote>his eye reviled me as his a. object,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 127</bibl></cit>, i. e. the object of his contempt.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>